sentences: Ian Matthias Bavitz (born June 5, 1976), better known by his stage name Aesop Rock, is an American rapper and producer residing in Portland, Oregon.
He was at the forefront of the new wave of underground and alternative hip hop acts that emerged during the late 1990s and early 2000s.

He was signed to El-P's Definitive Jux label until it went on hiatus in 2010.

His fourth studio album, None Shall Pass, was released on August 28, 2007.
His seventh record, Skelethon, was released on July 10, 2012.
His seventh release, The Impossible Kid, came out on April 29, 2016.
His eighth and most recent album, Spirit World Field Guide, came out on November 13, 2020.

Ian has two brothers: Christopher T. Bavitz (born 1973), a clinical professor at Harvard Law School and director of Cyberlaw Clinic at the Berkman Klein Center for Internet & Society, and Graham J. Bavitz (born 1978).
